      "source_url": "https://thaqalayn.net/hadith/22/2/15/2",
      "text": [
        ": سمعت أبا عبد الله وقد ذكر القائم ، فقلت: إني لأرجو أن يكون أمره في سهولة. فقال: لا يكون ذلك حتى تمسحوا العلق والعرق."
      ],
      "translations": {
        "en.abdullah-al-shahin": [
          "(3) Ali bin Ahmad al-Bandaneeji narrated from Obaydillah bin Musa al-Alawi from al-Hasan bin Mo’awiya from al-Hasan bin Mahboob from Eessa bin Sulayman that al-Mufadhdhal bin Umar had said: I heard Abu Abdullah as-Sadiq (as) mentioning al-Qa’im (as). I said: “I hope that his matter (rising) will be so easy.” He said: “It will be not so until you wipe blood and sweat together.”"
        ]
      }
    },
